2435	Grimm Tales: For Young and Old	Ralph Manheim, the highly acclaimed and  prize-winning translator, has rediscovered in the original  German editions of the Grimms' works the  unadorned, direct rhythm of the oral form in which they  were first recorded.	656	1983	\N	\N	9780385189507	https://images.gr-assets.com/books/1334781643m/254454.jpg
